olive oil
1 cucumber
1 bag snow peas
1 packet pork loin steaks
1 tin coconut milk
1 packet ponzu sauce
1 packet Crushed Peanuts
1 bag coriander
½ tin Thai green curry paste
1 bag Asian Slaw Mix
1 packet Yuzu Vinaigrette

• Roughly chop cucumber
• Trim the snow peas and thinly slice.

• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over medium-high heat. Season pork
• Cook pork until browned, 2-3 mins each side
• Add curry paste (1/2 tin for 2P/ 1 tin for 4P) and cook until fragrant, 1 min
• Add coconut milk, and cook until slightly thickened, 1-2 mins.

• In a bowl, combine slaw mix, cucumber, snow peas, ponzu and yuzu. Season
• Slice pork
• Divide slaw and pork between plates. Drizzle pork with sauce
• Serve with peanuts and torn coriander.